      "span_text": "The work of Greiner and co-workers has made the cell polarizing effects of FLT-3L quite clear and offer strong evidence that this factor (which was identified as a stem cell expansion factor using NOD/SCID mice which do not have good lymphoid reconstitution  ) is in fact a myeloid growth and differentiation factor, making its introduction into cultures attractive if the study of myeloid cells is the end goal."
